#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:3
msgid "What is pvr2fb?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:5
msgid ""
"This is a driver for PowerVR 2 based graphics frame buffers, such as the one "
"found in the Dreamcast."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:8
msgid "Advantages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:10
msgid ""
"It provides a nice large console (128 cols + 48 lines with 1024x768) without "
"using tiny, unreadable fonts (NOT on the Dreamcast)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:12
msgid "You can run XF86_FBDev on top of /dev/fb0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:13
msgid "Most important: boot logo :-)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:15
msgid "Disadvantages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:17
msgid "Driver is largely untested on non-Dreamcast systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:20
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:22
msgid ""
"You can pass kernel command line options to pvr2fb with `video=pvr2fb:"
"option1,option2:value2,option3` (multiple options should be separated by "
"comma, values are separated from options by `:`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:26
msgid "Accepted options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:29
msgid "font:X"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:29
msgid ""
"default font to use. All fonts are supported, including the SUN12x22 font "
"which is very nice at high resolutions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:33
msgid "mode:X"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:33
msgid ""
"default video mode with format [xres]x[yres]-<bpp>@<refresh rate> The "
"following video modes are supported: 640x640-16@60, 640x480-24@60, "
"640x480-32@60. The Dreamcast defaults to 640x480-16@60. At the time of "
"writing the 24bpp and 32bpp modes function poorly. Work to fix that is "
"ongoing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:40
msgid ""
"Note: the 640x240 mode is currently broken, and should not be used for any "
"reason. It is only mentioned here as a reference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:43
msgid "inverse"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:43
msgid "invert colors on screen (for LCD displays)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:45
msgid "nomtrr"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:45
msgid ""
"disables write combining on frame buffer. This slows down driver but there "
"is reported minor incompatibility between GUS DMA and XFree under high loads "
"if write combining is enabled (sound dropouts). MTRR is enabled by default "
"on systems that have it configured and that support it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:51
msgid "cable:X"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:51
msgid ""
"cable type. This can be any of the following: vga, rgb, and composite. If "
"none is specified, we guess."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:54
msgid "output:X"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:54
msgid ""
"output type. This can be any of the following: pal, ntsc, and vga. If none "
"is specified, we guess."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:59
msgid "X11"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pvr2fb.rst:61
msgid ""
"XF86_FBDev has been shown to work on the Dreamcast in the past - though not "
"yet on any 2.6 series kernel."
msgstr ""

